From williams snoopy Timothy Williams Subject Re viewing postscript files under X windows In article Kin Cho writes I wonder if anybody know of a X window based postscript file viewer that runs under SunOS prefered HPUX or IBM Reason I'm looking for this utility is that I've downloaded these large postscript documents and I'd like to know how useful and how long they are before commiting them to the printer and potentially wasting pages of paper and hogging the printer for Get ghostscript and Ghostview is a postscript previewer that uses From the ghostview README Ghostview An user interface for Ghostview is full function user interface for ghostscript Brief list of features Ghostview parses any known version of Adobe's Document Structuring Page size is automatically determined from the Document Structuring The user is able to override the values from the Window size is set to the bounding box for Encapsulated PostScript Default page size is Letter and can be changed via Xresources or application defaults file to or any other valid size for our European Scrollbars appear when Page orientation is automatically determined from the Document Structuring The user is able to override the values from the Ability to view at orientations Portrait Landscape Upside down and Seascape for those who rotate landscape the other direction Ability to preview in any supported Can preview in gray scale or color on a Color Ability to mark pages for printing or Good for people that printed a page document and lost page due to a printer Can popup zoom windows at printer resolution display dot printer dot The Ghostview distribution includes a Ghostview Widget that people are encouraged to use in other Ghostview is available via anonymous ftp from pub gnu ghostview pub ghostview From the ghostscript README This file describes version of An overview of Ghostscript Ghostscript is the name of a set of software that provides An interpreter for the Ghostscript language which very closely resembles the PostScript TM language and A set of C procedures the Ghostscript library that implement the graphics capabilities that appear as primitive operations in the Ghostscript The Ghostscript language interpreter and library are written entirely in C with some assembly language accelerators for MS DOS Currently Ghostscript is known to run on the following platform families IBM PC and compatibles with EGA VGA SuperVGA or compatible graphics under MS DOS or A wide variety of Unix systems using X Windows version release and including Sun Sun Sun Sun SPARCStation generic machines running ix H P and DECStation and VAX running Ultrix Sequent Symmetry Convex and Tektronix SGI Iris Indigo Sun workstations Sun SPARC Sun running SunView VAX VMS with gcc and DEC C compiler DEC C compiler version or later is required Get ghostscript from the same ftp site you get Tim Williams COM Night Vision Electronic Sensors Directorate DSN AMSEL RD NV VISPD Williams FAX Belvoir VA E MAIL